EOD API

General notes

EOD Api collection. For more info check https://eodhistoricaldata.com/knowledgebase/

API detail

Get Exchange Symbols

  • Curl
  • HTTP
curl -X GET "https://eodhistoricaldata.com/api/exchanges/:exchange-code?api_token={{API_KEY}}&fmt=csv"
GET /api/exchanges/:exchange-code?api_token={{API_KEY}}&fmt=csv HTTP/1.1
Host: eodhistoricaldata.com

Bulk Stock Details

  • Curl
  • HTTP
curl -X GET "http://eodhistoricaldata.com/api/bulk-fundamentals/NASDAQ?api_token={{API_KEY}}&offset=0&limit=10"
GET /api/bulk-fundamentals/NASDAQ?api_token={{API_KEY}}&offset=0&limit=10 HTTP/1.1
Host: eodhistoricaldata.com

Get Stock Details

Technical Indicator API

Split Adjusted Data

It’s not a technical indicator itself, but we added this function to our API. By default Open, High, Low and Close values (OHLC) we provide in raw values and adjust neither for splits nor for dividends. While ‘adjusted_close’ values are adjusted both to splits and dividends. However, if you need only split-adjusted closes, you can use this function to get the desired time series.

  • Curl
  • HTTP
curl -X GET "https://eodhistoricaldata.com/api/technical/:ticker?api_token={{API_KEY}}&function=splitadjusted&order=d&from=2020-01-01&to=today&fmt=json"
GET /api/technical/:ticker?api_token={{API_KEY}}&function=splitadjusted&order=d&from=2020-01-01&to=today&fmt=json HTTP/1.1
Host: eodhistoricaldata.com

AvgVolume

This function returns the Average Trading Volume. The average volume of a security over a longer period of time is the total amount traded in that period, divided by the length of the period.

  • HTTP

Intraday Historical Data API

Get intraday historical data

We support intraday historical data for major exchanges all around the world. Intraday data is limited now for 5-minute intervals and only the latest month. The data is updated 2-3 hours after market closing. For US symbols only NYSE and NASDAQ tickers are supported.

  • Curl
  • HTTP
curl -X GET "https://eodhistoricaldata.com/api/intraday/:ticker?api_token={{API_KEY}}&interval=5m&fmt=csv&from=&to="
GET /api/intraday/:ticker?api_token={{API_KEY}}&interval=5m&fmt=csv&from=&to= HTTP/1.1
Host: eodhistoricaldata.com

Bonds API

Get bond fundamental data

Only US corporate bonds supported. Bonds fundamentals and historical data could be accessed either via ISIN or via CUSIP IDs. Other IDs are not supported at the moment. Each symbol request costs 1 API call.

  • Curl
  • HTTP
curl -X GET "https://eodhistoricaldata.com/api/bond-fundamentals/:CUSIP?api_token={{API_KEY}}"

The API is the same as EOD Historical Data API for stocks, ETFs and Mutual Funds. Upcoming Splits

With our Financial Calendar data feed, we provide data about upcoming earnings, IPOs, and splits. If you are looking for an economic calendar, which includes earnings calendar and IPOs calendar, this API is for you.

  • Curl
  • HTTP
curl -X GET "https://eodhistoricaldata.com/api/calendar/splits?api_token={{API_KEY}}&from=2020-01-01&to=2020-04-01&fmt=json"

Options Data

Get stock options data

We provide stock options data for TOP US stocks from NYSE and NASDAQ. We have data for Options starting from April 2018. Options data is updated on daily basis, however, we do not provide a history for OPTIONS at the moment, it means that contracts with an expiration date before the current date are removed from the dataset. For example, for AAPL today (April 2, 2018) we have 622 PUT and CALL option contracts in our database. Each symbol request costs 1 API call.

  • Curl
  • HTTP
curl -X GET "https://eodhistoricaldata.com/api/options/:ticker?api_token={{API_KEY}}&from=2000-01-01&to=2020-04-01&trade_date_from&trade_date_to&contract_name"
GET /api/options/:ticker?api_token={{API_KEY}}&from=2000-01-01&to=2020-04-01&trade_date_from&trade_date_to&contract_name HTTP/1.1
Host: eodhistoricaldata.com

Live Stock Prices API

Get live stock prices

With this API endpoint you are able to get delayed (15-20 minutes) information about almost all stocks on the market. Each symbol request costs 1 API call. Multiple tickers request with 10 symbols costs 10 API calls.

  • Curl
  • HTTP
curl -X GET "https://eodhistoricaldata.com/api/real-time/:ticker?api_token={{API_KEY}}&fmt=json&s"
GET /api/real-time/:ticker?api_token={{API_KEY}}&fmt=json&s HTTP/1.1
Host: eodhistoricaldata.com
